A pilot pilot pulled his plane out of a terrifying North Sea nosedive with just seven seconds to spare .
The plane began to plunge after it was struck by lightning , but autopilot ignored the pilot 's commands to climb and tried to crash the plane into the sea .
The airliner pitched down , falling at 9,500 ft a minute , and fell to 1,100 ft above the ocean .
The aircraft landed safely in Aberdeen .